Privacy policy:

Effective date: July 21, 2023

This Privacy policy describes what data is collected and how it is used when using the camera on Android devices. We, Yelo LLC, adhere to the principles of protecting the privacy of users and are committed to ensuring the security and confidentiality of your data. Please read this policy carefully to fully understand how we process information received from your phone's camera.

1. Data collection:
We categorically do not collect any data from your device's camera and do not access images or videos created using the camera.

2. Data Usage:
Since we do not collect data from the camera, it is also not used by us for any purpose.

3. Permissions:
The application that you use to access the camera of your Android device may request the appropriate permissions for the camera functionality to work properly. We do not have access to these permissions and they are governed by the privacy policy and permissions of the app itself.

4. Data processing:
Since we do not collect or use data from the camera, no data processing is performed.

5. Third Party Access:
We do not provide access to your device's camera to any third parties, except in cases where this is required by law.

6. Security:
We take all reasonable measures to ensure the security of your data, including your phone's cameras. Our application does not collect, process or store data from the camera.

7. Changes to the Privacy Policy:
We reserve the right to update this privacy policy if necessary. In case of changes, we will publish an updated version of our application or important notifications.

8. Contact us:
If you have any questions or need additional information regarding the privacy policy or the operation of our application, please contact us at beisenadilov@gmail.com .
